HEADWORD: Outpreach
<hw>Out*preach"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To surpass in
preaching.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And for a villain's quick conversion⟦br⟧
A pillory can <qex>outpreach</qex> a parson.</q>
<rj><qau>Trumbull.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outprize</ent>⟦br⟧
